        "Title": "Cylance flagged components of Zoom on MacOS",
        "Description": "I noticed that backgrounds in Zoom no longer worked when I upgraded to Zoom 5.6.1 (560) on MacOS Catalina.  After playing around for quite some time, I checked Cylance and I see the following events.  Both tracked to when I did the original upgrade and a reinstall this morning.  We should either grant an exception for these files or ... well, do something if Zoom is dropping bad code.\r\n\r\n\"When\",\"Category\",\"Event\",\"Details\"\r\n4/16/2021 9:34:24 AM,Threat,Changed (Quarantined),/Users/mike/Library/Application Support/zoom.us/Plugins/aomhost.app/Contents/MacOS/aomhost\r\n4/13/2021 11:35:06 AM,Threat,Changed (Quarantined),/Applications/zoom.us.app/Contents/Frameworks/aomhost.app/Contents/MacOS/aomhost\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI'm leaving this ticket at high importance in case these files really are bad.\r\n\r\nHmm... my Cylance seems to be rather old.  Did someone turn off my account?  See attached screenshots.",
