                "PlanName": null,
                "ItemType": 9,
                "ItemID": 151542,
                "ItemTitle": "Cylance flagged components of Zoom on MacOS",
                "ReferenceID": null,
                "Body": "The application does not work correctly (Screen backgrounds do not work.  This plugin implements them).  Also note the last policy update on the screen shots I sent.  That does not seem correct.  Please verify I am getting policy updates or if I should not use Cylance.  If the application file is clean, then yes, I need an exception.",
                "UpdateType": 1,
                "NotifiedList": "Andrew Weisskopf <andy@UDel.Edu>, Ben Miller <millerbe@UDel.Edu>, Eric Eckman <eckman@UDel.Edu>, Shawn Cosgrove <scosgrov@UDel.Edu>, Tyrone Smith <tyrone@UDel.Edu>",
                "IsPrivate": false,
                "IsParent": false,
                "RepliesCount": 0,
                "ILike": false,
                "LikesCount": 0,
                "BreadcrumbsHtml": null,
                "HasAttachment": false
            },
            {
                "ID": 418806,
                "CreatedUid": "066b4b65-3fa5-e911-a81d-000d3a1808ae",
                "CreatedRefID": 50455,
                "CreatedFullName": "Tyrone Smith",
                "CreatedFirstName": "Tyrone",
                "CreatedLastName": "Smith",
                "CreatedByPicPath": null,
                "CreatedDate": "2021-04-19T15:28:34.963Z",
                "LastUpdatedDate": "2021-04-19T15:28:34.963Z",
                "ProjectID": 0,
                "ProjectName": null,
                "PlanID": 0,
                "PlanName": null,
                "ItemType": 9,
                "ItemID": 151542,
                "ItemTitle": "Cylance flagged components of Zoom on MacOS",
                "ReferenceID": null,
                "Body": "Changed Status from <b>Open</b> to <b>In Process</b>.<br /><br />I wasn&#39;t able your replicate the issue on BigSur OSX 11.2.3 Zoom 5.6.3 Cylance 2.1.1580\r\n\r\nHowever, I remember having similar issues previously with GnuPGP.  Most apps will continue to work properly with the quarantined files.  I think the flagging behavior is related to the security alerting function in the OS.   If the app does not work, please update the ticket.  These files do not appear to be malicious and we can work on creating exceptions if needed.\r\n\r\nThanks",
                "UpdateType": 2,
                "NotifiedList": "Michael Porter <mike@UDel.Edu>",
